neighbors.name: Gregg A. Komplin
neighbors.claims: Gregg A. Komplin owns multiple land parcels in the Town of Vienna, Dane County, including a 39-acre tract in Section 11 and a 20-acre tract in Section 11 ([source](https://www.apraz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/T.-Vienna-2024-Completed-Real-Estate-Assessment-Roll-1.pdf)). His properties are listed with a DeForest, WI mailing address ([source](https://www.apraz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/T.-Vienna-2024-Completed-Real-Estate-Assessment-Roll-1.pdf)). Komplin appears on proposed zoning maps for the Village of DeForest/Town of Vienna ETJ area ([source](https://hdp-us-prod-app-deforest-engage-files.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/3217/6797/2380/4_Proposed_Zoning_Map_2025.12.05.pdf)). No meeting minutes or local news were found in which Komplin has voiced any position on development or energy projects in the Town of Vienna or Dane County ([source](https://www.apraz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/T.-Vienna-2024-Completed-Real-Estate-Assessment-Roll-1.pdf)).
neighbors.influence_justification: Longtime landowner; donor to local Shrine club

approach_recommendations.engage: Have a trusted local farmer or community leader reach out to him, emphasizing respect for his farmland and addressing any concerns about preserving agricultural use.

neighbors.name: Jason D. Kelley
neighbors.claims: Jason D. Kelley is listed as the owner of a 1-acre parcel on County Highway DM in the Town of Vienna, Dane County, with an Arlington mailing address ([source](https://www.apraz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/T.-Vienna-2024-Completed-Real-Estate-Assessment-Roll-1.pdf)). He has been a recipient of USDA agricultural subsidies in Columbia County/Dane County region ([source](https://farm.ewg.org/top_recips.php?fips=55021&progcode=totalfarm&page=10)). There is no public record of Kelley speaking on development issues in Town of Vienna meeting minutes ([source](https://storage.googleapis.com/juniper-media-library/383/2025/09/Aug23.pdf)).
neighbors.influence_justification: Private resident; no public office found

approach_recommendations.engage: Engage him in a casual, neighborly conversation, listening to any personal concerns (e.g., traffic or noise). A low-key, one-on-one approach through a mutual acquaintance or friendly visit is likely to build trust.

neighbors.name: Gerald R. Hahn
neighbors.claims: Gerald R. Hahn owns multiple land parcels in the Town of Vienna, specifically along Patton Road and Wibu Road, often co-owned with family members ([source](https://www.apraz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/T.-Vienna-2024-Completed-Real-Estate-Assessment-Roll-1.pdf)). The Hahn family has longstanding ties to the area, evidenced by the local road named "Hahn Road" near their properties ([source](https://hdp-us-prod-app-deforest-engage-files.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/2817/6797/4783/3_Updated_Proposed_Zoning_Map.pdf)). In 2008, Hahn was involved in a zoning reclassification petition with Dane County ([source](https://board.danecounty.gov/documents/pdf/archived-reports/leg/REFFERALS-2008-2009.pdf)). The Town of Vienna Board has discussed infrastructure improvements on roads adjacent to his property, specifically culvert replacements on Patton and Hahn Roads in 2023 ([source](https://storage.googleapis.com/juniper-media-library/383/2025/09/Sept23.pdf)).
neighbors.influence_justification: Significant land holdings; family name on local infrastructure

approach_recommendations.engage: Ask a well-known local figure (such as a fellow veteran farmer or town official) to introduce the project to him, emphasizing minimal disruption and how it aligns with preserving the rural character of the land.
